x+y+z=2(a+b+c)=28
z:x:y=6:7:8
x=b+c,
y=a+c,
z=a+b.
z=6k
x=7k
y=8k
x+y+z=28
21 k=28
k=\frac{4}{3}
z=6k=8,
x=7k=\frac{28}{3},
y=8k=\frac{32}{3}.
a=a+b+c-x=\frac{14}{3},
b=a+b+c-y=\frac{10}{3},
c=a+b+c-z=6.
\frac{a+b}6=\frac{b+c}7=\frac{c+a}8=\frac{-(a+b)+(b+c)+(c+a)}{-6+7+8}=\frac{2c}9
\frac{a+b+(b+c)+(c+a)}{6+7+8}=\frac{2(a+b+c)}{21}
\implies \frac{2c}9=\frac{2(a+b+c)}{21}
a+b+c=14
